name: __new__
doc: Called to create a new instance of class. Rarely overridden; called before __init__.

name: __init__
doc: Initializer method called after an instance is created; used to set up object state.

name: __repr__
doc: Called by repr() to compute the “official” string representation of an object.

name: __str__
doc: Called by str() and print() to compute a nicely readable string representation of an object.

name: __len__
doc: Called by len() to return the length (number of items) of an object.

name: __eq__
doc: Called to implement equality comparison (==) between two objects.

name: __lt__
doc: Called to implement the ‘less-than’ comparison (<) between two objects.

name: __getitem__
doc: Called to implement retrieval of an item via indexing (e.g., obj[key]).

name: __setitem__
doc: Called to implement assignment to an indexed item (e.g., obj[key] = value).

name: __enter__
doc: Called at the beginning of a with-block (context manager); should return the context object.

name: __exit__
doc: Called at the end of a with-block (context manager); handles cleanup and accepts exception parameters.

name: __iter__
doc: Called by iter() to return an iterator object for the container.

name: __next__
doc: Called by next() (or implicitly by a for-loop) to retrieve the next item from an iterator.

name: __call__
doc: Called when the instance is “called” as a function (object()).

name: __name__
doc: The name of the module. When a module is run as the main program, its __name__ is set to "__main__".

name: __file__
doc: The pathname of the file from which the module was loaded, if it was loaded from a file.

name: __doc__
doc: The documentation string (if provided) for a module, class, method, or function.

name: __package__
doc: The package name for the module, used by the import system.

name: __add__
doc: Implements addition (x + y) for objects.

name: __sub__
doc: Implements subtraction (x - y) for objects.

name: __mul__
doc: Implements multiplication (x * y) for objects.

name: __truediv__
doc: Implements true division (x / y) for objects.

name: __floordiv__
doc: Implements floor division (x // y) for objects.

name: __mod__
doc: Implements modulo operator (x % y) for objects.

name: __pow__
doc: Implements exponentiation (x ** y or pow(x, y)).

name: __neg__
doc: Implements unary negation (-x) for objects.

name: __pos__
doc: Implements unary positive (+x) for objects.

name: __abs__
doc: Implements built-in abs(x) for objects.

name: __bool__
doc: Implements truth value testing for objects (bool(x)).

name: __copy__
doc: Implements shallow copy support (used by copy.copy()).

name: __deepcopy__
doc: Implements deep copy support (used by copy.deepcopy()).

name: __sizeof__
doc: Returns size of object in bytes, used by sys.getsizeof().

name: __mro__
doc: Tuple of classes that are considered when using method resolution order (MRO).

name: __bytes__
doc: Called by the built-in bytes() to compute a byte-string representation of an object.

name: __format__
doc: Called by the format() built-in (and format string syntax) to produce a formatted string representation of the object.

name: __abs__
doc: Implements the built-in abs() function for objects (return the absolute value).

name: __complex__
doc: Implements conversion to a complex number; called by built-in complex() when appropriate.

name: __int__
doc: Implements conversion to an integer; called by built-in int() when appropriate.

name: __float__
doc: Implements conversion to a float; called by built-in float() when appropriate.

name: __round__
doc: Implements the built-in round() function for objects, with optional ndigits parameter.

name: __index__
doc: Called to implement operator index; for objects usable as indices (e.g., in slicing, built-ins requiring integer index).

name: __hash__
doc: Implements built-in hash(), returning hash value for the object; used in dictionary keys, sets, etc.

name: __getattr__
doc: Called when attribute access fails (attribute not found) to allow custom behavior.

name: __setattr__
doc: Called when an attribute assignment is about to happen; allows interception of attribute setting.

name: __delattr__
doc: Called when an attribute deletion is about to happen; allows interception of attribute deletion.

name: __getattribute__
doc: Called unconditionally for attribute access (even when attribute exists); lowest-level attribute access hook.

name: __dir__
doc: Called by the built-in dir() to list attributes of an object; can be overridden to customize introspection.

name: __ge__
doc: Implements the “greater-than or equal” (>=) comparison between two objects.

name: __gt__
doc: Implements the “greater-than” (>) comparison between two objects.

name: __ne__
doc: Implements the “not equal” (!=) comparison between two objects; by default calls __eq__ and negates.

name: __radd__
doc: Implements reversed addition (y + x when x doesn’t support __add__), for objects.

name: __rand__
doc: Implements reversed bit-wise AND (&) operation, for objects.

name: __ior__
doc: Implements in-place bit-wise OR (|=) operation for objects.

name: __imul__
doc: Implements in-place multiplication (*=) operation for objects.

name: __bool__
doc: Called to determine truth value of the object; used when converting to bool or in if/while contexts.

name: __copy__
doc: Implements shallow copy behavior, used by copy.copy().

name: __reduce_ex__
doc: Implements pickling support; provides control over serialization behavior (called by pickle module).

name: __reduce__
doc: Implements pickling support; called by pickle to serialize an object (fallback to __reduce_ex__).

name: __slots__
doc: Class variable defining static list of allowed instance attributes, used to avoid per-instance __dict__ overhead.

name: __annotations__
doc: Dictionary containing variable annotations (PEP 484) for functions, classes, and modules.

name: __orig_bases__
doc: Tuple of original bases for a generic class before substitution of type arguments (typing module).

name: __getnewargs__
doc: Supports pickling of new style classes; returns arguments for object reconstruction.
